.TH CWE-78 7 "2026-06-15" "CWE Top 25 (2025)" "Software Weakness Reference"
.SH NAME
CWE\-78 \- Improper Neutralization of Special Elements used in an OS Command (OS Command Injection)
.SH RANK
2025 CWE Top 25 rank: \fB#9\fR (2024 rank: 7).
.SH CLASSIFICATION
Class: Injection.
.SH DESCRIPTION
Untrusted input is placed into a command run by a system shell without neutralising shell metacharacters (; | & $ ` etc.), letting an attacker append or alter commands and gain code execution with the app's privileges.
.SH MITIGATION
Avoid invoking a shell. Pass arguments as a vector to an exec\-style API so the OS treats them as data, not shell syntax. If a shell is unavoidable, strictly allow\-list input. Run with least privilege.
